 *
 * Tests row binders on 'yield' (issue #387). A binder names the whole
 * output row as a single scan-variable-like name; the row's fields
 * are reached through the name, and 'current' equals the name.
 *)

(*) Bind the row; output type is unwrapped, field access via 'r'.
from i in [{a=1,b=2}] yield r = i;
> val it = [{a=1,b=2}] : {a:int, b:int} list
(*) Access fields through the binder.
from i in [{a=1,b=2}] yield r = i yield r.a;
> val it = [1] : int list
(*) Bare field names are not in scope.
from i in [{a=1,b=2}] yield r = i where a > 0;
> stdIn:1.41 Error: unbound variable or constructor: a
>   raised at: stdIn:1.41
(*) 'current' equals the binder.
from i in [{a=1,b=2}] yield r = i where current.a > 0;
> val it = [{a=1,b=2}] : {a:int, b:int} list
from i in [{a=1,b=2}] yield r = i yield current.a;
> val it = [1] : int list
(*) A record expression becomes a single named row (not scattered).
from i in [{a=1,b=2}] yield r = {c = i.a + i.b};
> val it = [{c=3}] : {c:int} list
from i in [{a=1,b=2}] yield r = {c=i.a, d=i.b} where r.c > 0 yield r.d;
> val it = [2] : int list
(*) The binder combines with a following join into a record.
from i in [1,2] yield r = i + 1 join u in [3,4];
> val it = [{r=2,u=3},{r=2,u=4},{r=3,u=3},{r=3,u=4}] : {r:int, u:int} list
(*) Equality still available via parentheses.
from i in [1,2,3] yield (i = 2);
> val it = [false,true,false] : bool list

(*) End row-binder.smli
